associations in jobs instead of in-memory, turning errors into objects, and so much more.</p>

<p>It‚Äôs amazing how Rails has grown over the years and while we have some improvements to make to the
<a href="https://weblog.rubyonrails.org/2020/5/7/A-May-of-WTFs/">onboarding process</a>, Rails has never been better. The features
in this release focus on adding the functionality you need to keep your application up and running for years to come.</p>

<p>Let‚Äôs look at some of the new functionality:</p>

