<h2 id="delegated-types">Delegated Types</h2>

<p>Rails 6.1 adds ‚ÄúDelegated Types‚Äù as an alternative to single-table inheritance. This is helpful for representing class hierarchies allowing the superclass to be a concrete class that is represented by its own table. Each subclass has its own table for additional attributes. Check out the <a href="https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/39341">pull request</a> written by <a href="https://github.com/dhh">DHH</a>.</p>

