            </h2>
            <p class="entry-meta">
              Posted by <span class="vcard"><span class="fn">eileencodes</span></span>,
              <span class="published" title="2017-09-27 14:33:00 +0000">September 27, 2017 @  2:33 pm</span>
              
                <span class="categories">in
              
              
                  <a href="/releases/" rel="category tag">Releases</a>
              
              
                </span>
              
            </p>
          </header>
          <section>
<!-- Begin Post -->
<p>Hi everyone,</p>

<p>I am happy to announce that Rails 4.2.10 final has been released!</p>

<p>As noted in the rc1 post, Rails 4.2 is no longer supported except for severe security patches, but the last release introduced a couple regressions that warranted a release. Unless more regressions are found this will likely be the last bug fix release for Rails 4.2. <img class="emoji" title=":champagne:" alt=":champagne:" src="https://github.githubassets.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f37e.png" height="20" width="20"></p>

<h2 id="changes-since-429">CHANGES since 4.2.9</h2>

<p>The following gems had changes since 4.2.9. Changes are listed below, or you can read the CHANGELOG‚Äôs on GitHub:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/v4.2.10/actionpack/CHANGELOG.md">Action Pack CHANGELOG</a></li>
</ul>

<blockquote>
  <p>Fix regression in behavior of <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">normalize_path</code>.</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p>In Rails 5 there was a change to ensure the encoding of the original string
in a path was maintained. This was incorrectly backported to Rails 4.2 which
caused a regression.</p>
</blockquote>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/v4.2.10/activerecord/CHANGELOG.md">Active Record CHANGELOG</a></li>
</ul>

<blockquote>
  <p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Relation#joins</code> is no longer affected by the target model‚Äôs
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">current_scope</code>, with the exception of <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">unscoped</code>. Fixes #29338.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>The remaining gems (Action Mailer, Action View, Active Job, Active Model, Active Support, and Railties) had no changes.</p>

