        <article>
          <header>
            <h2>
              <a href="/2015/6/16/Rails-3-2-22-4-1-11-and-4-2-2-have-been-released-and-more/" rel="bookmark">Rails 3.2.22, 4.1.11 and 4.2.2 have been released and more</a>
            </h2>
            <p class="entry-meta">
              Posted by <span class="vcard"><span class="fn">rafaelfranca</span></span>,
              <span class="published" title="2015-06-16 17:02:42 +0000">June 16, 2015 @  5:02 pm</span>
              
                <span class="categories">in
              
              
                  <a href="/releases/" rel="category tag">Releases</a>
              
              
                </span>
              
            </p>
          </header>
          <section>
<!-- Begin Post -->
<p>Hi everyone!</p>

<p>Rails 3.2.22, 4.1.11 and 4.2.2 have been released, along with web console and jquery-rails plugins
and Rack 1.5.4 and 1.6.2.</p>

<p>These releases contain security fixes, so please upgrade as soon as possible!</p>

<p>The security fixes for 4.1.11 and 4.2.2 are:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rubyonrails-security/7VlB_pck3hU/3QZrGIaQW6cJ">CVE-2015-3226</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rubyonrails-security/bahr2JLnxvk/x4EocXnHPp8J">CVE-2015-3227</a></li>
</ul>

<p>In order to make upgrading as smooth as possible, we‚Äôve only included commits directly related
to each security issue.</p>

<p>The security fix for 3.2.22 is:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rubyonrails-security/bahr2JLnxvk/x4EocXnHPp8J">CVE-2015-3227</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Differently from the Rails 4 releases, Rails 3.2.22 includes all the commits from the 3-2-stable
branch. This mean that now Rails 3.2 supports Ruby 2.2.</p>

<p>The commits for 3.2.22 can be found <a href="https://github.com/rails/rails/compare/v3.2.21...v3.2.22">here</a>,
the commits for 4.1.11 can be found <a href="https://github.com/rails/rails/compare/v4.1.10...v4.1.11">here</a>,
and the commits for 4.2.2 can be found <a href="https://github.com/rails/rails/compare/v4.2.1...v4.2.2">here</a>.</p>

<h3 id="web-console">Web Console</h3>

<p>We are also releasing Web Console 2.1.3 that contains the fix for the following issue:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rubyonrails-security/lzmz9_ijUFw/HBMPi4zp5NAJ">CVE-2015-3224</a></li>
</ul>

<p>The commits can be found <a href="https://github.com/rails/web-console/compare/v2.1.2...v2.1.3">here</a>.</p>

<h3 id="jquery-ujs-and-jquery-rails">jquery-ujs and jquery-rails</h3>

<p>We are also releasing jquery-ujs 1.0.4 and jquery-rails 3.1.3 and 4.0.4 that includes fix for the
following issue:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rubyonrails-security/XIZPbobuwaY/fqnzzpuOlA4J">CVE-2015-1840</a></li>
</ul>

<p>The commits for jquery-rails 3.1.3 can be found <a href="https://github.com/rails/jquery-rails/compare/v3.1.2...v3.1.3">here</a>,
the commits for jquery-rails 4.0.4 can be found <a href="https://github.com/rails/jquery-rails/compare/v4.0.3...v4.0.4">here</a>,
and the commits for jquery-ujs 1.0.4 can be found <a href="https://github.com/rails/jquery-ujs/compare/v1.0.3...v1.0.4">here</a>.</p>

<h3 id="rack">Rack</h3>

<p>Rack 1.5.4 and Rack 1.6.2 have also been released, which include fixes for the
following issue:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rubyonrails-security/gcUbICUmKMc/qiCotVZwXrMJ">CVE-2015-3225</a></li>
</ul>

<p>The commits for rack 1.5.4 can be found <a href="https://github.com/rack/rack/compare/1.5.3...1.5.4">here</a>,
and the commits for rack 1.6.2 can be found <a href="https://github.com/rack/rack/compare/1.6.1...1.6.2">here</a>.</p>

<h2 id="sha-1">SHA-1</h2>

<p>Here are the checksums for Rails 3.2.22:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ shasum *3.2.22*
cc56be2f49baeeccc0da87b740f23d0ac7bd2d24  actionmailer-3.2.22.gem
d20fd24d9049fad99ea5405a265ca7c9690af378  actionpack-3.2.22.gem
