        <article>
          <header>
            <h2>
              <a href="/2008/9/3/rails-2-0-4-maintenance-release/" rel="bookmark">Rails 2.0.4: Maintenance release</a>
            </h2>
            <p class="entry-meta">
              Posted by <span class="vcard"><span class="fn">David</span></span>,
              <span class="published" title="2008-09-03 08:43:00 +0000">September 3, 2008 @  8:43 am</span>
              
                <span class="categories">in
              
              
                  <a href="/releases/" rel="category tag">Releases</a>
              
              
                </span>
              
            </p>
          </header>
          <section>
<!-- Begin Post -->
<p>Thanks to Git it‚Äôs been a lot easier to maintain older branches of the code base, so we‚Äôve taken the opportunity to backport a bunch of bug fixes to the 2.0 branch and here‚Äôs the release for that.</p>
<p>The only major issue is that we‚Äôve fixed the <span class="caps">REXML</span> DoS vulnerability with a monkey patch that ships in the box. So if you‚Äôre on 2.0 and haven‚Äôt dealt with the issue already, you can upgrade to 2.0.4 and get it fixed.</p>
<p>You can install with: <code>gem install rails --version 2.0.4</code></p>
<p><a href="http://gist.github.com/8565">See all the changes</a></p>
<p><b><span class="caps">UPDATE</span>:</b> The actual 2.0.4 gem didn‚Äôt get published yesterday due to a bug in the release script. It‚Äôs been fixed and 2.0.4 is actually available on the main gem repository. Sorry about that!</p>
<!-- End Post -->
          </section>
        </article>


        <article>
